# Editorial voice — pointer

The brand voice, persona, and writing rules live in
[`EDITORIAL_VOICE.md`](../../EDITORIAL_VOICE.md) at the repo root.

**Always read it before:**
- Authoring or editing any user-facing copy (hotel fiches, guides, rankings, FAQ, AEO blocks, emails, meta tags, llms.txt).
- Writing or modifying any LLM prompt that produces French/English/Spanish/German/Italian copy (pipelines in `scripts/editorial-pilot/src/**`).
- Designing a new content block, callout, or editorial section component.

The deeper production grammar (banned lexicon, syntactic patterns, gate QA
metrics) lives in [`docs/editorial/style-guide.md`](../../docs/editorial/style-guide.md).
The two documents are **complementary** — see
[`EDITORIAL_VOICE.md`](../../EDITORIAL_VOICE.md) §6 Compatibility for the
three open conflicts to arbitrate before the brief fully supersedes the
legacy style guide.

## Hard rules surfaced here (do not re-derive)

- **Concierge voice** — expert complice, jamais commercial, toujours précis. Not a journalist, not a salesperson — an insider sharing operational secrets.
- **Always TTC, always euros** in any price mention.
- **Sentence length ≤ 25 words** (see §6 conflict C2 against the journalistic-density rule in `style-guide.md` §9).
- **`## ⭐ Le Conseil du Concierge`** block at the end of every hotel fiche — 60-90 words, opens with a concrete operational secret (a room number, a timing, an access route).
- **Banned superlatives**: `incroyable`, `magnifique`, `exceptionnel` (except Atout France classification), `magique`, `sublime`, plus the 75+ patterns in `style-guide.md` §4-5.
- **Cultural references**: Atout France (with year), Michelin (with star count), Relais & Châteaux, Leading Hotels of the World, Forbes Travel Guide — never vague mentions.
- **Multilingual**: same Concierge voice, culturally adapted (never machine-translated literally). Numbers, addresses, distances must match the FR canonical version verbatim.

## Where the voice gets enforced in code

- **LLM prompts**: `scripts/editorial-pilot/src/**/prompts/*.md` (the `01-draft-factuel.md`, `03-humanisation-magazine.md`, `05-correctrice-post-fact-check.md`, etc.). New brief rules must be folded into these prompts to take effect on the next regenerate.
- **Component skeleton**: the 9-section fiche skeleton (`EDITORIAL_VOICE.md` §4) must map cleanly onto the 15-block CDC §2 contract in [`.cursor/rules/hotel-detail-page.mdc`](hotel-detail-page.mdc). The editorial sections are blocks 4 (description longue) + 11 (FAQ).
- **Gate QA** (post-LLM validator): metrics in `style-guide.md` §9. New brief rules become hard fails only after C1/C2/C3 are arbitrated.
